# clangd configuration. The C shims include project headers from include/ with
# quotes (e.g. "fsparse_proto.h"), which clangd cannot find from the .c file's
# own directory. Point clangd at the CMake compile_commands.json for exact
# flags, and add include/ as a fallback when no build tree is present. System
# headers (<suitesparse/umfpack.h>, <superlu/slu_ddefs.h>) resolve via the
# default /usr/include search path and need no extra flags.
CompileFlags:
  CompilationDatabase: build
  Add: [-Iinclude]
